attributes.title: contributors_growth_help
attributes.visState:
{"title":"contributors_growth_help","type":"markdown","params":{"fontSize":12,"markdown":"* This panel focuses on **Contributors Growth** in terms of **number of people contributing to the several data sources of the project**.
* **The big number** gives an overview of the total and unique contributors across all of the data sources in the selected time range (using timepicker located at the top right corner of the dashboard).
* **Top right evolutionary chart** shows the evolution of the active contributors over time (line) and the difference between a given slot of time and its predecessor. Periods of time where the growth has been positive are represented in green, while periods with negative growth are displayed in yellow.
* **Bottom right evolutionary chart** displays the number of contributors over time. Red line displays the average of the community in the timeframe of analysis. The bars represents how far that period of time is from the average. The value of each bar is the difference between the number of contributors in that slot of time and the average of contributors for that period of time.
* **Table** splits all of this information by data source. This gives the number contributors.

[See complete panel documentation](https://bitergia.gitlab.io/panel-collections/open_source_program_office/contributors-growth.html)"},"aggs":[]}

attributes.title: ocean_contributions_help
attributes.visState:
{"title":"ocean_contributions_help","type":"markdown","params":{"fontSize":12,"markdown":"* This panel focuses on **Engagement** in terms of **number of contributions**.
* **Heat map** allows to find most active organizations and which projects they are targeting their contributions to.
* **Bar charts** show evolution of contributions in total and stacked by data source and allows to identify the general trend and local trends based on moving averages.

[See complete panel documentation](https://bitergia.gitlab.io/panel-collections/open_source_program_office/engagement-contributions-overview.html)"},"aggs":[]}

attributes.title: ocean_tickets_efficiency_timing_help
attributes.visState:
{"title":"ocean_tickets_efficiency_timing_help","type":"markdown","params":{"fontSize":12,"markdown":"This panel focuses on time to first attention and time to close tickets.

**Bar chart** compares the difference in average between first attention and closing time of tickets created in a given time frame. Ideal case would be low values for both, which means contributors are attended soon and tickets are closed in a reasonable time. Worst case would be having long bars for both, which means customers have to wait a long time to get our first attention and also closing time is of course longer than desired.

**Trends** in bar chart give an idea about where are we going to.

**Gauges** show times in average and median to complement bar chart with a more general view.

[See complete panel documentation](https://bitergia.gitlab.io/panel-collections/open_source_program_office/efficiency-timing-overview.html)"},"aggs":[]}

attributes.visState:
{"title":"quick tips throubleshooting","type":"markdown","params":{"markdown":"### Quick Tips / Troubleshooting
* **If you see no data at all**, please double-check the time range selected on the right-hand side of the search bar.
* Almost every chart allows you to click or drag and drop to generate filters and drill down the data.
* Sharing button in Kibana doesn't work for now, only public Cauldron visualizations are available for sharing. Go to your project page and copy the "Public dashbord link".","fontSize":14,"openLinksInNewTab":true},"aggs":[]}

attributes.title: Welcome Message
attributes.visState:
{"aggs":[],"params":{"fontSize":13,"markdown":"### Welcome to your Cauldron.io Workspace 

In this **read-only** space we have built many visualizations. Don’t be discouraged. The goal is to demonstrate that data is available for you and to spark your imagination. These visualizations probably do not meet your specific needs. We encourage you to change these default assembly of visualizations to what you need.

There is a **private workspace** for exploring your data and no one else can get to it. Think of it as your secret alchemist office where you brew potions (data) in Cauldron. [Here you have the instructions to get there](https://community.cauldron.io/t/prepare-your-workspace-required-steps-before-building-custom-visualizations-and-dashboards/20). Don't spread the secret 🤫

For now you can not **share** dashboards you have created, but you can share a link with our fancy dashboards with your data. You can obtain that link from your project page.

Enjoy brewing your potions (i.e., explore your data)!

Your Cauldron.io Team

P.S.: We would love to hear your feedback. Tell us what you love and where we can improve. Just [open a new topic in our feedback forum](https://Community.Cauldron.io/c/support-feedback/) or, if you want to send us a private note, email [contact@cauldron.io](mailto:contact@cauldron.io).

#### Some useful links:
Go to the [User Guide and Documentation](https://Community.Cauldron.io/c/docs) for instructions on how to get started. You will also find [recipes](https://community.cauldron.io/c/docs/metrics-visualization-recipes/7) that describe how to produce specific visualizations and metrics. 

The [Cauldron Community forum](https://Community.Cauldron.io/c/support-feedback/) is a great place to ask questions, get help, and help others. Check it out!

Finally you can [join the Cauldron newsletter](https://mailchi.mp/003f1e1f6242/cauldron-newsletter).","openLinksInNewTab":true},"title":"Welcome Message","type":"markdown"}
